[49m[38;5;9m- 25    [0m:[38;5;9m[49m **AWS Step Functions for orchestration.** The pipeline has branching logic (clinician review or not, regeneration loop for readability failures, different delivery channels per patient preference). Step Functions makes the state machine explicit and observable. For operational teams, being able to see which step a given summary is stuck in is invaluable.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     25[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **AWS Step Functions for orchestration.** The pipeline has branching logic (clinician review or not, regeneration loop for readability failures, different delivery channels per patient preference). Step Functions makes the state machine explicit and observable. For the clinician-review branch, use the `waitForTaskToken` callback pattern: the Lambda that completes generation hands off a task token when it routes to review; the review UI calls `SendTaskSuccess` with the signed summary (or `SendTaskFailure` if the clinician rejects it). This avoids polling and supports extended review SLAs without burning execution time. For operational teams, being able to see which step a given summary is stuck in is invaluable.
