[49m[38;5;9m- 27    [0m:[38;5;9m[49m **Amazon EventBridge for note-signed events.** Triggering generation from the EHR's note-signed event (via an integration layer) is more reliable than polling. EventBridge routes the event to the pipeline's Step Functions workflow.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     27[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon EventBridge for note-signed events.** Triggering generation from the EHR's note-signed event (via an integration layer) is more reliable than polling. EventBridge routes the event to the pipeline's Step Functions workflow. Because EventBridge delivers at-least-once, your pipeline needs an idempotency gate at the entry point. Derive a deterministic fingerprint from `(encounter_id, note_version_or_signed_at)`, attempt a DynamoDB conditional write with `attribute_not_exists(fingerprint)`, and skip if the fingerprint already exists. Without this, duplicate note-signed events produce duplicate summaries, duplicate LLM charges, and duplicate patient deliveries.
